        GALA DINNER
    </div>

    <!-- Characteristics Section -->
    <div class="characteristics-section">
        A gala dinner is a formal event often associated with conferences, award ceremonies, or significant celebrations.
        <br><br>
        Typical characteristics of a gala dinner:
        <ul>
            <li><span>Formality:</span> Gala dinners are <span>high-profile</span> and formal. Attire is typically black-tie or evening wear, reflecting the event’s elegance.</li>
            <li><span>Purpose:</span> They are usually designed for <span>formal occasions</span>, such as recognizing achievements or hosting conferences. Gala dinners often include keynote speeches, presentations, and formal awards.</li>
            <li><span>Program:</span> The evening includes a multi-course meal and structured program, with speeches or presentations taking center stage. The focus is on honoring achievements or facilitating important discussions.</li>
            <li><span>Entertainment:</span> Entertainment is often sophisticated, such as live performances or speeches, aligning with the event's formal tone.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

